								<div class="block-correspondence" id="1494">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>The essay &ldquo;<a href="/article/179">Killing Time</a>,&rdquo; by Stephen J. Lyons [November 2006], was a mirror to my own life. As a thirty-something woman, I know that my corporate position is a necessary facet of my existence. I still give time to my other side, however, the side that throws caution to the wind and enjoys an enlightened bohemian life. Together, the two give me balance.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Kimberly Richardson<br>Memphis, Tennessee</p>
					</blockquote>
